  "prompt": "I don't talk in English. How do I talk in English?",
  "response": "If you're looking to learn how to speak in English, here are some steps you can follow:\n\n1. **Start with the Basics**: Learn common greetings, phrases, and simple vocabulary. This will help you begin conversations.\n\n2. **Practice Regularly**: Try to practice speaking English every day. You can do this by talking to yourself, reading aloud, or using language-learning apps.\n\n3. **Listen to English**: Exposure to English through music, movies, podcasts, and conversations will help you understand pronunciation and intonation.\n\n4. **Join a Class**: Consider enrolling in English classes where you can practice speaking with a teacher and other learners.\n\n5. **Find a Language Partner**: Connect with someone who speaks English and wants to learn your language. This way, you can practice together.\n\n6. **Use Language Learning Apps**: Apps like Duolingo, Babbel, or HelloTalk can help you practice speaking and improve your skills.\n\n7. **Don\u2019t Be Afraid to Make Mistakes**: Making mistakes is a natural part of learning a new language. Use them as opportunities to improve.\n\n8. **Expand Your Vocabulary**: Gradually learn new words and phrases to build your confidence in speaking.\n\n9. **Stay Consistent**: Learning a language takes time, so be patient and consistent in your practice.\n\nGood luck!",
